==Coworking Space==
If you're planning on starting a space or just want to see some coworking resources, check out:
*The productive conversation taking place on the [https://groups.google.com/forum/#!forum/coworking Coworking Google Group].  One of our interns cataloged all the topics discussed in 2000+ posts on this group - you can view her spreadsheet [https://spreadsheets0.google.com/a/sarapisfoundation.org/spreadsheet/pub?key=0ArhSktWsQi1VdGRCXzFhSHlpaG5kYlZYX1o5bG11SkE&output=html here] or download it from [http://www.sarapisfoundation.org/index.php/lets-collab/downloads our website]. Our intern also produced the [[OS Handbook]], a synthesis of knowledge she gleaned from her research.
*The relatively unorganized resources at the [http://wiki.coworking.info/w/page/16583831/FrontPage coworking wiki].
*Polished resources about starting a space from the [http://socialinnovation.ca/sssi Center for Social Innovation] and [http://coherecommunity.com/ebooks Cohere Coworking].
*A [http://sarapisfoundation.org/index.php/lets-collab/downloads/cat_view/7-free-documents Coworking Financial Model] that helps people create a business plan for their space.

If you're seriously considering opening a coworking or hacker/maker space, we suggest contacting the [http://schoolfactory.org/ School Factory].  They'll provide you a wide range of support, including a fiscal sponsorship so you can raise tax free money through them, consulting services and exposure to some of the coolest people in the collaborative space movement.

